AB  - In this paper, the effects of increases in trade taxes on the steady-state values of consumption and the capital stock per worker are examined in an economy which faces variable terms of trade and where the price-taking consumer intertemporally maximizes utility. In addition, the optimal trade tax for such an economy is derived.
